Global solar distribution company d.light opened its regional office and service centre in Eldoret on April 26 at Kipps Plaza, off Iten Road. The office will serve Uasin Gishu county and its environs. The event was officiated by Governor Jackson Mandago and global d.light CEO Ned Tozun. Mandago praised d.light solar for championing renewable solar energy, creating jobs for the youth and leveraging on innovation and technology to uplift the community. He urged the public to help fight counterfeits and only buy genuine solar products.